answers.answer: I am assuming the 743 is one of the liver enzymes from your liver function test.  I would clarify with your doctor what the 743 was for or even better obtain a copy of the bloodwork for yourself.  I am going to bet that it is either the AST or ALT and with that sort of an elevation a doctor will usually first test for viral hepitatis.  If you doctor hasn't then he needs to get his butt in gear.

question: I asked my doctor last week to check me for diabetes since I 've been feeling bad lately and it's a fear of mine since it runs on both sides of my family. My blood work came back no concern of diabetes but my liver count was extremely high at 743. I don't drink or take meds on a regular basis do I have reason to be worried?
title: Do I have reason to worry?
